    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"meaning\" is just something we make up to distract ourselves from the fact that it's all meaningless. if you look at the math of it, we're just temporary arrangements of atoms that won't even leave a trace. how can anyone say connection or emotions matter when they're just chemical reactions in a brain that's eventually going to be dust? it feels like we're just performing a play for an empty theater.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
